                            <comment id="252165" author="adilger" created="Mon, 29 Jul 2019 08:27:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are a bunch of other places that &lt;tt&gt;skip_env&lt;/tt&gt; is incorrectly used, in particular for &lt;tt&gt;$MDSCOUNT&lt;/tt&gt; and other places that are just variations in the test configs, and not shortcomings in the Lustre autotest environment.  I &lt;em&gt;guess&lt;/em&gt; we could force all tests to run with multiple MDTs, but I don&apos;t think that is the case today.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be interesting to at least try one test run with &lt;tt&gt;$FAIL_ON_SKIP_ENV=true&lt;/tt&gt; and see what fails.  Ideally once these patches are run and any resulting failures are fixed, then we could enable this by default in the future?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
